message: >-
  If you use these patterns in your systems, research, or publications,
  please cite this repository using the metadata below.
type: software
title: >-
  finserv-agent-audit: Governance Patterns for Autonomous AI
  Agents in Regulated Financial Services
authors:
  - family-names: Bhaduri
    given-names: Kunjar
    orcid: ""
    affiliation: North Texas Capital Investments
    website: "https://linkedin.com/in/kunjarbhaduri"
repository-code: "https://github.com/linus10x/finserv-agent-audit"
url: "https://github.com/linus10x/finserv-agent-audit"
abstract: >-
  Reference governance patterns, schemas, agents, and runnable
  implementations for audit-ready autonomous AI agents in regulated
  financial services. Covers autonomy-level classification (A0 through
  A4) — a proprietary governance framework documented in this repository
  — along with DEFCON-style risk-state degradation, sovereign veto
  architecture, shadow-mode rollout, tamper-detecting hash-chain audit
  logging (within-trust-boundary), four Protocol seams for audit-chain
  integrity (LedgerStore, TimestampSource, WitnessRegister, MIProxy),
  VendorScoreGate for third-party AI scoring drift detection, and the
  FSI-specific governance gates (ModelInventory for SR 11-7,
  AdverseActionGate for FCRA + CFPB Circular 2022-03, SARWorkflowAudit
  for BSA/AML, EquityAudit for ECOA/Reg B, BestInterestCheck for SEC
  Reg-BI, ProtectedClassProxyDetector mutual-information arm). v1.3 adds
  seven new governance modules covering the discrimination frontier and
  third-party vendor surface (LDASearchHarness, LLMDisparateImpactHarness,
  EffectiveChallengeHarness, VendorAttestationLedger, RetrainingCadenceMonitor,
  DeprecationWatch, CustomerFacingChatbotGuardrail), the foundation-model
  API vendor-clauses (sixth vendor class), and six new regulatory +
  incident + disclosure docs (NYDFS Part 500 AI mapping, CFPB AI lending
  supervisory landscape, CFPB Circular 2023-09 mapping, State-AG
  enforcement matrix, AI incident retrospective template, Disclosure
  artifact templates). Maps to twenty-plus regulatory frameworks including
  SR 11-7, OCC 2011-12 (historical) + OCC 2026-13 overlay, GLBA, FCRA,
  ECOA, BSA/AML, SOX 404 ITGC, SEC 17a-4, SEC Reg-BI, CFPB Circular
  2022-03, CFPB Circular 2023-09, NYDFS Part 500, NIST AI RMF, NIST AI
  600-1 GenAI Profile, Treasury FS AI RMF, ISO/IEC 42001, COSO ICAIR,
  EU AI Act 2024/1689, and multiple state-AG AI enforcement matters.
  Patterns were extracted from a multi-year private quantitative
  options research program with Marcos López de Prado as named advisor
  on adjacent work; the source program operates in paper-trading
  Phase 0 — no live capital has been deployed.
keywords:
